Well, we have that logic already:
```
if (session.exists(remoteFilePath)) {
				if (FileExistsMode.FAIL.equals(mode)) {
					throw new MessagingException(
							"The destination file already exists at '" + remoteFilePath + "'.");
				}
				else {
					if (this.logger.isDebugEnabled()) {
						this.logger.debug("File not transferred to '" + remoteFilePath + "'; already exists.");
					}
				}
				rename = false;
			}
```
Perhaps we don't need anything else since by default it assumes that you'd like to replace existing file. Therefore delete in case of first rename attempt.

I guess the fix has to be just like this:
