@lukass77 I believe `State` is your object that holds value to the gauge.
`ref -> ref.get().getValue()` is a lambda representing how to provide values to the gauge. `ref` is `stateRef` object passed from the second parameter in the method in this example.
So, it extracts the `State` from `AtomicReference`, then feeds the value to the gauge by calling `getValue()`.

