@tkvangorder wrote:

>  It appears that we are using a custom class loader (to pick up these artifacts) when loading the environment: https://github.com/openrewrite/rewrite-maven-plugin/blob/main/src/main/java/org/openrewrite/maven/AbstractRewriteMojo.java#L73 So, that would explain why it is finding the recipe. However, I think because we are also importing rewrite classes into the Mojo, these classes are going to be loaded with the plugin's class loader. I honestly didn't know we had added this ability. I think many folks have been using the rewrite:configure to add the plugin to pom.xml and then rewrite:remove to remove it. I know this is not quite the same experience.I think we will have to investigate/unify how class loading is done before this will work correctly.


