> ClassGraph instances allow overriding the classpath/classloaders that are scanned, so making ClassGraph use the set of jars that are used to construct the recipe should be possible.  It seems to me that in general you would want to prefer the recipe's classpath rather than the plugin or the project you're operating on but there are probably usecases I'm not aware of

But it sounds like Tim's solution sounds simplest (if it works): " The maven plugin has init and remove goals to at least for now make it a two step: first init by itself, then run and remove together as a second step."

