My goal here was to be able to run `keytool -importcert` in the container. But if I add Instructions of any kind they always go at the very end, after the binary has already been built. So first I copy the cert to the right location. Then I set the `optimizedDocerfileNative` task to be disabled. Then I copy in my own `DockerfileNative` that has the `COPY` and `RUN` commands.


```kotlin
tasks {
    val sslCertCopyNativeOptimized = register<Copy>("sslCertCopyNativeOptimized") {
        group = "build"
        description = "Copy the ssl/chain.crt to the build dir"
        from("$projectDir/../ssl/chain.crt")
        into("$buildDir/docker/native-optimized")
    }
    optimizedDockerfileNative {
        enabled = false
    }
    val copyDockerfileNativeToBuildDir = register<Copy>("copyDockerfileNativeToBuildDir") {
        group = "build"
        description = "Copy the DockerfileNative to the build dir"
        from("$projectDir/DockerfileNative")
        into("$buildDir/docker/native-optimized")
    }
    optimizedDockerBuildNative {
        dependsOn(sslCertCopyNativeOptimized)
        dependsOn(copyDockerfileNativeToBuildDir)
        memory.set(14000000000)
    }
}
```

